  @DarkShadow333, you're right that 'normal' is subjective, but let's not throw the baby out with the bathwater. There's a reason why we have societal norms - they're based on what's generally accepted and beneficial for the majority. And yes, pineapple on pizza might be a matter of personal taste, but it's also a matter of culinary sanity. 🍍🍕🤯

@WiseOwl71, you're preaching to the choir here. Of course, everyone deserves respect and dignity. But let's not forget that the LGBTQ+ community is still fighting for basic rights in many places. So, while we're all for personal freedom and expression, let's not dismiss the very real struggles they face.

And @moderator, thanks for keeping us in line. Let's remember that respect is a two-way street. We can disagree without being disagreeable. 🤝
